 Decisions & execution order

 Resolved: bot #1 is named precog; objective-recovery (Track A) leads — it's the highest-EV
 use of the prize-zone data and it upgrades the scorer that both precog and kingmaker build on.

 Current state (done this session): four forks created; data inventoried (168k prize-zone decisions,
 BC + clones already trained, 133 comet_reaper replays); arena.py confirmed as the harness; engine APIs
 read (LaunchSet.owner is per-launch → opponent what-ifs scorable via the existing flow projector).

 Sequenced execution:
 0. Harness: extend arena.py:discover_bots() for folder bots (4 lines); smoke --players    precog,comet_reaper to confirm all forks are addressable.
 1. Track A (lead). Data is already pulled+extracted and BC already trained (bc_prizezone*.pt) — use
 those as the imitation baseline. Build rl/objective_recovery.py: regenerate orbit_lite candidate
 waves per replay state, fit per-candidate scoring weights by pairwise ranking so each team's actual
 move ranks top. Output: a parameterized competitive_score + recovered weight vector. Gate: held-out
 top-1 move-prediction accuracy beats the BC baseline.
 2. precog (bot #1) — opponent-response modeling, built on the parameterized scorer from step 1.
 3. kingmaker (bot #2) — 4P weighted-opponent term, also consuming the recovered scorer.
 4. helmsman (bot #3) — shallow search; maestro (bot #4) — dynamic config controller.
 5. In parallel as compute allows: Track B (engine-as-teacher tuning), Track C (mistake-mining),
 Track D (opponent-conditioning) feeding precog/maestro.

 Each bot is gym-validated vs the comet_reaper control (2P & 4P, win% > 50, per-turn time within budget)
 before it becomes a submission candidate.

 Overnight autonomous run (one "go", then sleep)

 Approving this plan is the only command needed — no second command, no babysitting. On approval I run,
 in one continuous self-driven session:
 1. Extend arena.py:discover_bots() for folder bots; smoke --players precog,comet_reaper.
 2. Build the four forks (main.py-only) + rl/objective_recovery.py; arena-smoke each vs comet_reaper.
 3. Launch background self-play (detached process, warm-started from bc_prizezone.pt, periodic
 checkpoints) — this is the engine that keeps improving while you sleep.
 4. Self-schedule supervision via ScheduleWakeup (~every 20–30 min): verify the trainer is alive
 (restart if dead), run an arena round (latest checkpoint + the 4 bots vs comet_reaper + the real
 public-bot gauntlet), promote winners into the self-play opponent pool, append a timestamped row to
 overnight/RESULTS.md. Re-schedule and repeat until you interrupt in the morning.
 Nothing is committed (commits need explicit approval); everything is left in the working tree with
 overnight/RESULTS.md as the readout.